Privacy Policy for Baritone

Effective Date: 24/12/2024

This Privacy Policy describes how Baritone collects, uses, and shares information when you use our Discord bot. By using the Bot, you agree to the collection and use of your information in accordance with this Privacy Policy. If you do not agree with this policy, do not use the Bot.

1. Information We Collect
We may collect the following types of information when you use the Bot:

a. User-Provided Information
Commands: When you interact with the Bot, the Bot may collect the commands you enter. This includes any requests, inputs, or messages sent to the Bot.
Usernames and IDs: The Bot may store basic information such as your Discord username and unique user ID for the purposes of responding to commands and interactions.
Server Information: If the Bot is added to a server, we may collect basic information about the server, including the server name, server ID, and list of users in the server.
b. Usage Data
Command Usage: We may collect data on which commands are used most frequently, errors that occur, or performance metrics related to your interactions with the Bot.
Activity Logs: In some cases, the Bot may store logs of user activity for troubleshooting, analytics, and improving the Bot’s performance.
If your Bot offers additional features like music streaming, custom settings, or external integrations, we may collect further data based on user input, such as playlists, preferences, or settings configurations.

2. How We Use Your Information
The information we collect is used for the following purposes:

To Provide Bot Services: We use the data to fulfill your requests and respond to your commands, such as moderation tasks, game features, or any other functionality provided by the Bot.
To Improve Bot Functionality: We analyze usage data to improve the performance and reliability of the Bot, fix bugs, and enhance user experience.
To Communicate with Users: We may use your information to provide updates about Bot features, server issues, or other relevant notices.
Security and Compliance: We may use your information to ensure compliance with our Terms of Service and to prevent malicious use or abuse of the Bot.
3. Data Storage and Retention
Data Storage: The data we collect may be stored on servers located in your Country/Region or other regions. We use secure systems to store your information and prevent unauthorized access.
Retention: We may retain your information for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes described in this Privacy Policy. Data may be deleted upon user request or after it is no longer needed for the Bot’s functions.
4. Data Sharing and Disclosure
We do not sell, trade, or otherwise share your personal information with third parties, except in the following situations:

With Service Providers: We may share data with trusted third-party service providers who assist us in operating the Bot or providing services to you. These service providers are required to maintain the confidentiality of your information.
Legal Compliance: We may disclose your information to comply with applicable laws, regulations, or legal requests, or to protect our rights, safety, or property.
Business Transfers: If the ownership or control of the Bot changes (e.g., through acquisition or merger), your information may be transferred as part of that transaction.
5. Your Data Rights
You have the following rights with respect to the data we collect:

Access: You can request a copy of the information we have collected about you.
Correction: If any of your information is inaccurate or incomplete, you can request that it be corrected.
Deletion: You may request the deletion of your personal data from our system, subject to certain limitations.
Opt-Out: If you no longer wish to interact with the Bot, you can remove the Bot from your Discord server or stop using the Bot.
To exercise these rights, please contact us via the contact information provided at the end of this policy.

6. Security
We use reasonable physical, technical, and administrative measures to protect the information we collect. However, no method of transmission over the internet or electronic storage is 100% secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.

7. Third-Party Links
The Bot may provide links or references to third-party websites, applications, or services. These third-party services have their own privacy policies, and we are not responsible for their content or practices. We encourage you to review the privacy policies of any third-party services before interacting with them.

8. Children's Privacy
Our Bot is not intended for children under the age of 13. If we become aware that we have inadvertently collected personal information from a child under 13, we will take steps to delete that information as soon as possible.

9. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update or modify this Privacy Policy at any time. Any changes will be posted on this page with the revised effective date. We encourage you to review this policy periodically for any updates. Your continued use of the Bot after any changes constitutes your acceptance of the updated Privacy Policy.

10. Contact Information
If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, or if you would like to exercise your rights regarding your data, please contact us at:

